-- int_deduped_billing.sql
```sql
-- Intermediate: Remove duplicate billing events per subscription/month
WITH source AS (
    SELECT
        subscription_id,
        event_month,
        amount,
        event_type,
        ROW_NUMBER() OVER (
            PARTITION BY subscription_id, event_month
            ORDER BY event_id DESC
        ) AS row_num
    FROM {{ ref('stg_billing_events') }}
)
SELECT
    subscription_id,
    event_month,
    amount,
    event_type
FROM source
WHERE row_num = 1
```

-- int_subscriptions_enriched.sql
```sql
-- Intermediate: Enrich subscriptions with user company and plan tier
WITH source AS (
    SELECT
        s.subscription_id,
        s.user_id,
        s.plan_id,
        s.started_at,
        s.ended_at,
        s.status,
        COALESCE(p.tier, '(unknown)') AS tier,
        COALESCE(c.industry, '(unknown)') AS industry
    FROM {{ ref('stg_subscriptions') }} s
    LEFT JOIN {{ ref('stg_users') }} u
        ON u.user_id = s.user_id
    LEFT JOIN {{ ref('stg_companies') }} c
        ON c.company_id = u.company_id
    LEFT JOIN {{ ref('stg_plans') }} p
        ON p.plan_id = s.plan_id
)
SELECT
    subscription_id,
    user_id,
    plan_id,
    started_at,
    ended_at,
    status,
    tier,
    industry
FROM source
```

-- fct_monthly_subscription_metrics.sql
```sql
-- Mart: Monthly subscription metrics by tier and industry
WITH billing_base AS (
    SELECT
        subscription_id,
        event_month,
        amount
    FROM {{ ref('int_deduped_billing') }}
)
SELECT
    DATE_TRUNC('month', b.event_month)::DATE AS month,
    se.tier,
    se.industry,
    COUNT(DISTINCT se.subscription_id) AS active_subscriptions,
    SUM(b.amount) AS total_mrr,
    COUNT(DISTINCT se.user_id) AS unique_users
FROM billing_base b
LEFT JOIN {{ ref('int_subscriptions_enriched') }} se
    ON se.subscription_id = b.subscription_id
GROUP BY
    DATE_TRUNC('month', b.event_month)::DATE,
    se.tier,
    se.industry
ORDER BY
    month DESC,
    tier,
    industry
